      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 years of technology consulting. Thousands of whiteboards. Two daughters who still aren’t convinced I have a real job.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;According to my kids, I get paid to &amp;ldquo;talk and draw boxes.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They aren&amp;rsquo;t wrong. After two and a half decades in the industry, I’ve realized that the most complex problems in the world are usually just a bunch of messy, disconnected boxes waiting for someone to draw the right lines between them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
